content: I do not have a preference for any historical landmarks to visit. however, choosing which one to visit first may depend on the preferences of the visitor. if you are interested in ancient history, colchester castle or sutton hoo are great places to start. if you are interested in medieval architecture, norwich cathedral or ely cathedral are the best options. if you want to explore the beauty of english stately homes, sandringham house, blickling hall, or houghton hall are some of the top options. ultimately, it is the visitor's interests and priorities that will dictate what must-see historical landmarks to visit first.
